laboratory_examinations.findings: Pancreas homogeneously enhancing, diffuse edema within retroperitoneum and anterior pararenal space. No pseudocyst, no splenic vein thrombosis, normal liver, spleen, adrenal glands. Duodenum contains a diverticulum; no signs of obstruction or inflammation. Common bile duct normal in size, 10-mm stone within gallbladder neck.
